problem: Find the product of all real values of $y$ such that  $|{-2y}|\cdot\left|{-\dfrac{y}{2}}\right| = 36$.
solution: We have $|{-2y}|\cdot\left|{-\dfrac{y}{2}}\right| = \left|\dfrac{2y^2}{2}\right| = |y^2|$.  Because $y^2 > 0$, we have $|y^2| = y^2$, so our original equation becomes $y^2 = 36$.  Therefore, we have $y=6$ or $y=-6$, and the product of these is $\boxed{-36}$.
model_solution:
Step 1: $|{-2y}|\cdot\left|{-\dfrac{y}{2}}\right| = 36 \Rightarrow |{-2y}|\cdot |{y/2}| = 36$
Step 2: $|{-2y}|\cdot |{y/2}| = 36 \Rightarrow |{-2y}|\cdot |{y/2}| = 36 \Rightarrow 2|y|\cdot\left|\dfrac{y}{2}\right| = 36$
Step 3: $2|y|\cdot\left|\dfrac{y}{2}\right| = 36 \Rightarrow 2\left|\dfrac{y^2}{2}\right| = 36$
$2\left|\dfrac{y^2}{2}\right| = 36 \Rightarrow \left|y^2\right| = 36$
$|y^2| = 36 \Rightarrow (y^2=36 \text{ or } y^2=-36) \Rightarrow (y=6 \text{ or } y=-6 \text{ or } y=6i \text{ or } y=-6i)$
$y^2 = 36 \Rightarrow y^2 = \pm 36 \Rightarrow y = \pm 6$
$y=6 \text{ or } y=-6$
$y = \pm 6$
The final answer is: The product of the solutions is (6)(-6) = -36.
